---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="query_architecture_graph — ArchLens"
  description="Query the indexed architecture model as a graph: summaries, node lookups, neighborhoods, paths, and impact slices."
>
  <section class="tool-page">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="tool-page-header">
        <h1 class="tool-page-title">query_architecture_graph</h1>
        <span class="tool-page-badge">Query</span>
      </div>

      <p class="tool-page-intro">
        The graph query interface for the indexed model. Use it to summarise the full graph,
        find nodes by label and property filters, traverse neighborhoods, trace shortest paths
        between components, and compute change-impact slices. The graph includes applications,
        components, entrypoints, interfaces, containers, runtime flows, data-flow paths, sinks,
        and their typed edges. Start with <code>action: "summary"</code> to orient yourself,
        then drill into specific nodes or paths.
      </p>

      <h2 class="tool-section-label">Arguments</h2>
      <table class="arg-table">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Name</th><th>Type</th><th>Required</th><th>Description</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>action</td>
            <td>string</td>
            <td>—</td>
            <td>One of <code>summary</code>, <code>find_nodes</code>, <code>find_edges</code>, <code>neighborhood</code>, <code>paths</code>, <code>impacted_by</code>. Default: <code>summary</code>.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>label</td>
            <td>string</td>
            <td>—</td>
            <td>Node label for <code>find_nodes</code> (e.g. <code>Component</code>, <code>Entrypoint</code>); edge label for <code>find_edges</code> (e.g. <code>DEPENDS_ON</code>).</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>query</td>
            <td>string</td>
            <td>—</td>
            <td>Free-text node search.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>filters</td>
            <td>object</td>
            <td>—</td>
            <td>Property filters. Supports exact match, partial text, and numeric comparisons like <code>{`{"confidence":"<=0.6"}`}</code>.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>nodeId</td>
            <td>string</td>
            <td>—</td>
            <td>Required for <code>neighborhood</code> and <code>impacted_by</code>.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>fromId / toId</td>
            <td>string</td>
            <td>—</td>
            <td>Required for <code>paths</code>.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>maxDepth</td>
            <td>integer</td>
            <td>—</td>
            <td>Traversal depth for <code>paths</code> or <code>impacted_by</code>.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>limit</td>
            <td>integer</td>
            <td>—</td>
            <td>Cap result set size. Omit to return all matches.</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2 class="tool-section-label">Example</h2>
      <div class="terminal-card">
        <div class="terminal-top">
          <span></span><span></span><span></span>
          <strong>tools/call</strong>
        </div>
        <pre><code>{`{
  "name": "query_architecture_graph",
  "arguments": {
    "action": "find_nodes",
    "label": "Component",
    "filters": { "agentCategory": "core-workflow" }
  }
}`}</code></pre>
      </div>

      <h2 class="tool-section-label">Output</h2>
      <p class="tool-page-intro">
        Depends on <code>action</code>. <code>summary</code> returns counts and top-level
        stats. <code>find_nodes</code> returns matching node records with all properties.
        <code>neighborhood</code> returns the subgraph around a node. <code>impacted_by</code>
        returns all nodes reachable from a given node — useful for change-impact analysis
        before modifying a repository or service.
      </p>

      <h2 class="tool-section-label">Related tools</h2>
      <div class="related-pills">
        <a href="/tools/index-workspace" class="related-pill">index_workspace</a>
        <a href="/tools/trace-data-flow" class="related-pill">trace_data_flow</a>
        <a href="/#tools" class="related-pill">find_components</a>
        <a href="/#tools" class="related-pill">render_architecture_view</a>
      </div>

      <a href="/#tools" class="tool-back-link">← All tools</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
